The paper discusses the optimization of carbon nanotube field-effect transistors (CNFETs) for building energy-efficient digital systems, which involves exploring and optimizing CNT processing options and CNFET circuit design. This falls under the categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET), electromagnetism (cs.EM), digital circuits (cs.DC), and architecture (cs.AR).
